    <custom_item>
      type                 : REGISTRY_SETTING
      description          : "DTOO131 - Word - Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins."
      info                 : "By default, if an application is configured to require that all add-ins be signed by a trusted publisher, any unsigned add-ins the application loads will be disabled and the application will display the Trust Bar at the top of the active window. The Trust Bar contains a message that informs users about the unsigned add-in."
      solution             : "The policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Microsoft Office Word 2007 -> Word Options -> Security -> Trust Center 'Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins' will be set to 'Enabled'."
      reference            : "800-171|3.13.13,800-53|SC-18(4),CAT|II,CSF|DE.CM-5,ITSG-33|SC-18(4),Rule-ID|SV-18223r2_rule,STIG-ID|DTOO131,Vuln-ID|V-17187"
